INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_body`, `blog_image`, `blog_author`, `blog_date`) VALUES
(31, 'Heading', '<h1><strong class=\"ql-font-monospace\">Integrating Vision Pro with Zoho Lens&nbsp;</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></h1><p>Now, let’s talk about how this powerful tech co</p><p>mbo works. Zoho Lens, a leading AR remote assistance tool, enables technicians to see exactly what customers see in real-time. With Vision Pro, this experience becomes extraordinary. Here’s how:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.zoho.com/blog/lens/zoho-lens-and-apple-vision-pro.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Enhanced visualization</strong></a><strong>:</strong> Vision Pro’s high-res displays and spatial awareness allow you to view detailed augmented reality overlays, making diagnostics easier.</li><li><strong>Seamless collaboration:</strong> Real-time AR interaction means you and your customers can collaborate more effectively, thanks to Vision Pro’s advanced sensors.</li><li><strong>Augmented instructions:</strong> Digital markers and annotations can be overlaid directly onto equipment, making instructions clearer and simpler to follow.</li></ul><h3><strong>Why this combo rocks&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>First off, Apple Vision Pro\'s spatial computing prowess lets you interact with digital content in the most intuitive way possible. Now, pair this tech with Zoho Lens\'s already impressive AR capabilities. We\'re talking about a support</p><p>experience where you can virtually pop into the customer\'s world, see exactly what they see, and provide laser-precise instructions.</p><h3><strong>In the real world</strong></h3><p><strong>For customers:</strong> Let\'s say your air conditioner goes kaput in the middle of summer. Instead of sweating it out waiting for help, you fire up Zoho Lens on your phone. On the other end, a technician using Apple Vision Pro gets a cl</p><p class=\"ql-align-center\"><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-right\"><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-right\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\">ear view of your AC. They guide you through the fix step-by-step, overlaying instructions and markers directly onto the live view.</p><p><strong>For technicians:</strong> Picture this: you\'re tasked with supporting a large-scale construction project during a critical compliance audit. The stakes are high, and any delays could push back your timeline, costing you money by the day. With Zoho Lens and Apple Vision Pro, you can provide remote inspection and access a live feed of the site instantly, even if you\'re miles away. You can zoom in, annotate, and offer real-time support as if you\'re physically present at the site. Vision Pro\'s displays are so clear and precise that they almost feel ethereal.&nbsp;</p>', '1727175616681.jpg', 'max', '2024-09-24 05:30:16');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_body`, `blog_image`, `blog_author`, `blog_date`) VALUES
(32, '5 New Additions to OneAuth for an Improved Apple Experience', '<p>With iOS 18, Apple\'s focus on customization enables users to personalize their Apple devices.</p><p>Zoho OneAuth is here to support that focus. Our new additions (available from day one) will give you the full flavor of Apple\'s customization and the convenience in authentication that OneAuth is known for.&nbsp;</p><p>Convinced? You can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://zurl.to/TBqAapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">download Zoho OneAuth</a>&nbsp;and enjoy the benefits of an improved authentication experience in your Apple devices.&nbsp;</p><p>Want to know more about what we have in store? Here are the new additions.</p><h2><strong>1. Seamless Account Recovery with Passkeys&nbsp;</strong></h2><p>Passkeys are no longer just for logins. During the iOS 16 update, passkeys improved the login experience across Zoho apps by offering a secure and passwordless sign-in.</p><p>With iOS 18, passkeys now support cloud syncing of TFA accounts and ensure smooth account recovery. Whether your device is lost, stolen, or you\'re migrating to a new one, you can easily recover your accounts. It also ensures convenience without compromising on security.</p><p><em>(Available on iOS, iPadOS and macOS Sequoia)</em></p><p><em><img src=\"https://blog.zohowebstatic.com/sites/zblogs/images/accounts/oaappleiosfeatures/1.png\"></em></p><h2><br></h2><h2><strong>2. Easy Login with Autofill for Verification Codes&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></h2><p>When you\'re logging into an app and need your TFA code, generally, you switch between the OneAuth app where you receive the code, and the app you\'re trying to log into. This switch is time-consuming and disrupts your workflow.</p><p>With iOS 18, Zoho OneAuth\'s autofill for verification codes eliminates the need to toggle between apps. You can now simply tap and paste the TFA code directly from the Apple keyboard, streamlining authentication without any app switching.</p><p><em>(Available on iOS, iPadOS and macOS Sequoia)</em></p><p><em><img src=\"https://blog.zohowebstatic.com/sites/zblogs/images/accounts/oaappleiosfeatures/2.png\"></em></p><h2><br></h2><h2><strong>3. Quick Access with OneAuth Widgets&nbsp;</strong></h2><p>With iOS 18, you can now add OneAuth widgets to quick actions like—Smart Sign-In, Restrict Sign-In, and Add New Account—to your Control Center, Lock Screen, or Action Button. This gives you faster, more convenient access to key features directly from your home screen.</p><ul><li><strong>Smart Sign-In:</strong>&nbsp;Instantly gain access to your QR scanner without having to open the OneAuth app.</li><li><strong>Restrict Sign-In:</strong>&nbsp;Enable or disable restrict sign-in to prevent unauthorized future sign-ins for added security.</li><li><strong>Add New Account:</strong>&nbsp;Add new TFA accounts to OneAuth quickly.</li></ul><p>These widgets enable you to navigate directly to the OneAuth app from the control center, which streamlines the sign-in process.</p><p><em>(Available on iOS and iPadOS)</em></p><p><em><img src=\"https://blog.zohowebstatic.com/sites/zblogs/images/accounts/oaappleiosfeatures/3.png\"></em></p><h2><br></h2><h2><strong>4. Customize Your iPad Navigation&nbsp;</strong></h2><p>With this year\'s Apple update, you can now personalize your iPad navigation using the floating tab bar and sidebar features in Zoho OneAuth.</p><p>The floating tab bar lets you customize the view with the features you use most frequently, making app navigation more straightforward and efficient.</p><p>Additionally, the sidebar provides quick access to key actions, such as adding new accounts, thus helping you stay organized.</p><p>These updates make it easier to tailor the app to your preferences, improving overall navigation.</p><p><em>(Available on iPad)</em></p><p><em><img src=\"https://blog.zohowebstatic.com/sites/zblogs/images/accounts/oaappleiosfeatures/4.png\"></em></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', '1727413717930.png', 'Dravid', '2024-09-27 05:08:38');

